communities, to allow for the privatization of social sector land. Willem Assies, &#8213;Land tenure and 
tenure regimes in Mexico: an overview&#8214;,<i> Journal of Agrarian Change</i>, vol. 8, No. 1, p. 33. 
</p>
<p> 22  See Geoffrey Payne, &#8213;Urban land tenure policy options: titles or rights?&#8214;, <i>Habitat International</i>, 
